      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAR DAN BUDDY (9) has been ultra consistent with a string of wins and placings to his name, finishing runner-up to Eureka winner Bay Of Biscay last start after charging home to win the City of Melton Plate. Comes in fresh but races well that way and while he draws on the back row he is dangerous with sit-and-sprint tactics so look for him late. Tasmanian TRIEDTOTELLYA (1) has hasn't raced for eight weeks since a win from the back row at Launceston but owns a strong fresh record. Loves this distance and should enjoy a soft run from the ace draw. SPEAK THE TRUTH (6) hasn't fired in two standing start outings off a spell but he was runner-up in the final of this series last year so expect him to be peaking for it again. Tricky draw for FIGHTER COMMAND (11) but he has won four of five tries at this distance and three of five fresh attempts so he is a player with luck. CAPTAIN RAVISHING (3) is an accomplished pacer stepping out for a new yard. Draws well so keep safe.",
